<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5008389>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 2. Orosarcophaga ornata postabdomen.(A) Male postabdomenin profile.(B) Fifth sternite;arrow indicates a cushion-like protuberance.(C) Phallic complex in profile (lectotype). (D) Phallus in ventral view (lectotype); arrow indicates an elongated process on the medial stylus. Scale bar: 1 mm. Abbreviations: ap pg, postgonal apodeme; bas, basiphallus; cer, cercus; ep, epandrium; hyp, hypandrium; ju, juxta; phal, phalapodeme; pog, postgonite; preg, pregonite; S 7 + 8, syntegosternite 7 + 8; stl, lateral stylus;st m, medial stylus;sur,surstylus;ves,vesica." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/5008389/files/figure.png" .

